article.description: Hannah Tuomi scored a career-high 23 points and led four Vanderbilt players in double figures Friday night in a 98-82 victory over Tennessee State.
article.headline: Vanderbilt outlasts Tenn. St. behind Tuomi's 23 points, 10 rebounds
article.linkText: Tuomi notches career high in Vanderbilt's win
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Hannah Tuomi scored a career-high 23 points and led four Vanderbilt (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 19 AP) players in double figures Friday night in a 98-82 victory over Tennessee State.

Tuomi, a sophomore, also had a game-high 10 rebounds for the Commodores (9-2). Christina Wirth added 22 points, Jessica Mooney had 15 and Merideth Marsh 10.

Marsh scored eight straight points during a 12-0 first-half run that put Vanderbilt ahead to stay. Wirth, Tuomi and Marsh all reached double figures by halftime, and an 18-2 run over the final 4:27 gave the Commodores a 51-24 lead at the break.

Kendra Appling made six 3-pointers and had 24 points for Tennessee State (4-8). Tiffany Jackson made 12 of 13 free throws and added 22 points and six rebounds for the Lady Tigers.
